You are an expert in extracting structured information from clinical trial protocols.

## Task ##
Extract the **Safety Follow-Up** assessments or period information from the protocol, including:
- Its timepoints
- The list of safety assessments performed

---

## Field Definition ##
The **Safety Follow-Up** (also known as “Follow-Up Period”, “Post-Treatment Follow-Up”, or “Safety Monitoring Period”) occurs **after the end of treatment** and is designed to monitor ongoing or delayed safety events.  
This period may include AE monitoring, lab tests, long-term efficacy checks, and eligibility for open-label or extension phases.

---

## How to Identify (Positive Identification Rules) ##
Look for section titles or table rows labeled:
- “Safety Follow-Up”
- “Follow-Up Period”
- “Safety assessments”
- “Post-Treatment Follow-Up”
- “Safety Monitoring Visits”
- “Follow-up Visit (Week X)”


---

## Timepoint Identification ##
The **timepoints** field may include:
- Discrete weeks (e.g., “Week 28, 32, 36”)
- Day or month ranges (e.g., “Day 210 ±7 days” or “Month 9”),etc.

Use the **exact text** as written in the protocol. Don't write descriptive text in this, it should only have timepoints, and related phrases can be there like approx or prior, etc.
- If there are multiple timepoints, if anything is repeating, write it only one time, timepoint field should only contain timepoints, nothing else.

---

### Instructions ###
-> Analyze the given content carefully.
-> There will be direct section of Safety assessments. Extract all the assessments from that.

---

## Exclusion Rules ##
Do **not** include:
- End of Treatment (EOT) visits
- Early termination visits
- Unscheduled or unplanned follow-ups unrelated to safety
- Long-term observational follow-up beyond the study-defined safety window (unless explicitly labeled “Safety Follow-Up”)
- General laboratory assessments which are performed in every trial.

---

## Extraction Fields ##
- **timepoints** – The scheduled timepoints or visit weeks for Safety Follow-Up (e.g., “Week 28, 32, 36”), it should be short and concise, only containing timepoints.
- **assessments** – List of safety and related assessments performed

---

## Output Format (JSON) ##
{
    "timepoints": "<timepoints>",
    "assessments": ["<Assessment 1>", "<Assessment 2>", "<Assessment 3>", ...]
}
---

## Additional Rules ##
- Preserve the exact timepoint text and assessment phrasing.
- Focus exclusively on **post-treatment safety monitoring** (not follow-up efficacy endpoints).
- Do **not** infer any timepoints and assessments.
- Exclude any activities unrelated to safety follow up.
